# Welcome to the Dynatrace Workshop! 
## Answers, Analytics, and Automation for Unified Observability and Security

![](https://mkt-cdn.dynatrace.com/assets/Marketing/dynatrace-dash-hero.png)

# Topics
* Grail - Dynatrace's data lakehouse purpose for observability data. It acts as a single unified storage solution for logs, metrics, traces, events, in full context!
* Dynatrace Query Language - Unlock answers from the goldmine of observability and security data in Dynatrace!
* Automation Engine - Proactive prevention, efficient operation, auto-remediation, automated quality checks, and route/report!
* App Engine - If you can dream it, you can build it!

This notebook will be your guide today with all of the relevant info you need. We will not cover every lab in the workshop today. After we cover the logs/basics section, we can do a "chose your own adventure" based on which data types/features you want to dig into. The workshop is designed to give you the building blocks to understand and use the new platform. You will have access to this demo environment until Aug 25 so you can keep playing around and working on the additional exercises. 

Feel free to reach out to me if you have any questions after the workshop!
[https://www.linkedin.com/in/jason-ostroski/](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jason-ostroski/)

# Login to Environment jja01219.apps.dynatrace.com
* Use your work email that you used to register for the event with. 
* Raise your hand if you cannot login.

### Learn how to navigate the environment
* Use the launcher
* Open apps - Everything's still here!
* Switch from light to dark mode

# Log Lab: How can we get answers from Logs?

Create a new notebook and let's start analyzing logs!
Build the below queries in the new notebook, learning how to query and analyze the data.

sections.markdown: ### I want to extract user, product and quantity, but we didn't set up parsing/processing rules before the logs were ingested. No worries! DQL to the rescue!

sections.title: Log Lab: Parse On Read - UserId, ProductId, ProductQuantity

input.value:
Fetch logs
|filter contains(content, "AddItemAsync")
|parse content, "LD 'userId='LD:userId', productId='LD:ProductId', quantity='INT:ProductQuantity"
|fields ProductId, ProductQuantity, userId

| filter contains(content, "AddItemAsync")
| parse content, "LD 'userId='LD:userId', productId='LD:ProductId', quantity='INT:ProductQuantity"
| fields ProductId, ProductQuantity, userId

input.value:
fetch logs 
| filter k8s.container.name == "frontend" and k8s.namespacename == "hipstershop"
| parse content, "JSON:jsonContent"
| fieldsAdd timestamp, 
  method = jsonContent[http.req.method],
  path = jsonContent[http.req.path],
  bytes = jsonContent[http.resp.bytes],
  status = jsonContent[http.resp.status],
  response_time = jsonContent[http.resp.took_ms],
  message = jsonContent[message],
  sessionID = jsonContent[session],
  loglevel = jsonContent[severity], 
  currency = jsonContent[currency]
| sort timestamp desc
| filter message == "request complete"
